learning_outcomes.en:
By finishing the course, the student:
-	understands and reproduces the sounds of the Kazakh alphabet, building a foundation for pronunciation and phonetic accuracy;
-	uses essential Kazakh vocabulary and basic grammar to communicate in everyday situations (greetings, introductions, ordering food, etc.);
-	recognizes and constructs simple sentences in Kazakh, including basic verb conjugations and common sentence structures;
-	reads and writes basic Kazakh text using the Cyrillic alphabet;
-	demonstrates familiarity with Kazakh cultural norms, values, and etiquette for respectful communication;
-	identifies key Kazakh phrases in listening exercises and responds appropriately in conversational practice.
